SECOND REGULAR SESSION
HOUSE BILL NO. 3345
103RD GENERAL ASSEMBLY
INTRODUCED BY REPRESENTATIVE EALY.
7187H.01I JOSEPH ENGLER, Chief Clerk
AN ACT
To amend chapter 217, RSMo, by adding thereto one new section relating to correctional
facility interactions by members of the general assembly.
Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the state of Missouri, as follows:
Section A. Chapter 217, RSMo, is amended by adding thereto one new section, to be
2 known as section 217.267, to read as follows:
217.267. Beginning January 1, 2027, and each year thereafter, each member of
2 the general assembly shall be required to conduct at least four qualifying department of
3 corrections interactions per year, which shall qualify under one or both of the following
4 categories:
5 (1) In-person visits to any department of corrections facility in this state; or
6 (2) Communication with an inmate regarding any issue the inmate is
7 experiencing at a department of corrections facility, which shall include resolution of
8 such issue.
✔
EXPLANATION — Matter enclosed in bold-faced brackets [thus] in the above bill is not enacted and is
intended to be omitted from the law. Matter in bold-face type in the above bill is proposed language.

